#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:3
msgid "NixOS virtual machines"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:5
msgid ""
"One of the most important features of NixOS is the ability to configure the "
"entire system declaratively, including packages to be installed, services to "
"be run, as well as other settings and options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:7
msgid ""
"NixOS configurations can be used to test and use NixOS using a virtual "
"machine, independent of an installation on a \"bare metal\" computer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:9
msgid "What will you learn?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:11
msgid ""
"This tutorial serves as an introduction to creating NixOS virtual machines. "
"Virtual machines are a practical tool for experimenting with or debugging "
"NixOS configurations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:14
msgid "What do you need?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:16
msgid "A Linux system with virtualisation support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:17
msgid ""
"(optional) A graphical environment for running a graphical virtual machine"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:18
msgid "A working [Nix installation](https://nix.dev/install-nix)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:19
msgid "Basic knowledge of the [Nix language](reading-nix-language)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:22
msgid ""
"A NixOS configuration is a Nix language function following the [NixOS module]"
"(https://nixos.org/manual/nixos/stable/index.html#sec-writing-modules) "
"convention. For a thorough treatment of the module system, check the []"
"(module-system-deep-dive) tutorial."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:26
msgid "Starting from a default NixOS configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:29
msgid ""
"This tutorial starts with building up your `configuration.nix` from first "
"principles, explaining each step. If you prefer, you can skip ahead to the "
"[sample configuration](sample-nixos-config) section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:33
msgid "We start with a minimal `configuration.nix`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:35
msgid ""
"{ config, pkgs, ... }:\n"
"\n"
"{\n"
"  boot.loader.systemd-boot.enable = true;\n"
"  boot.loader.efi.canTouchEfiVariables = true;\n"
"\n"
"  system.stateVersion = \"24.05\";\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:46
msgid ""
"To be able to log in, add the following lines to the returned attribute set:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:48
msgid ""
"  users.users.alice = {\n"
"    isNormalUser = true;\n"
"    extraGroups = [ \"wheel\" ];\n"
"  };\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:55
msgid ""
"Additionally, you need to specify a password for this user. For the purpose "
"of demonstration only, you specify an insecure, plain text password by "
"adding the `initialPassword` option to the user configuration:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:58
msgid "   initialPassword = \"test\";\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:62
msgid "We add two lightweight programs as an example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:64
msgid ""
"  environment.systemPackages = with pkgs; [\n"
"    cowsay\n"
"    lolcat\n"
"  ];\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:72
msgid ""
"Do not use plain text passwords outside of this example unless you know what "
"you are doing. See [`initialHashedPassword`](https://nixos.org/manual/nixos/"
"stable/options.html#opt-users.extraUsers._name_.initialHashedPassword) or "
"[`ssh.authorizedKeys`](https://nixos.org/manual/nixos/stable/options."
"html#opt-users.extraUsers._name_.openssh.authorizedKeys.keys) for more "
"secure alternatives."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:76
msgid "Sample configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:78
#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:218
msgid "The complete `configuration.nix` file looks like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:80
msgid ""
"{ config, pkgs, ... }:\n"
"{\n"
"  boot.loader.systemd-boot.enable = true;\n"
"  boot.loader.efi.canTouchEfiVariables = true;\n"
"\n"
"  users.users.alice = {\n"
"    isNormalUser = true;\n"
"    extraGroups = [ \"wheel\" ]; # Enable ‘sudo’ for the user.\n"
"    initialPassword = \"test\";\n"
"  };\n"
"\n"
"  environment.systemPackages = with pkgs; [\n"
"    cowsay\n"
"    lolcat\n"
"  ];\n"
"\n"
"  system.stateVersion = \"24.05\";\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:101
msgid "Creating a QEMU based virtual machine from a NixOS configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:103
msgid "A NixOS virtual machine is created with the `nix-build` command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:105
msgid ""
"$ nix-build '<nixpkgs/nixos>' -A vm -I nixpkgs=channel:nixos-24.05 -I nixos-"
"config=./configuration.nix\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:109
msgid ""
"This command builds the attribute `vm` from the `nixos-24.05` release of "
"NixOS, using the NixOS configuration as specified in the relative path."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:0
msgid "Detailed explanation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:113
msgid ""
"The positional argument to [`nix-build`](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/stable/"
"command-ref/nix-build.html) is a path to the derivation to be built. That "
"path can be obtained from [a Nix expression that evaluates to a derivation]"
"(derivations)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:116
msgid ""
"The virtual machine build helper is defined in NixOS, which is part of the "
"[`nixpkgs` repository](https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs). Therefore we use "
"the [lookup path](lookup-path-tutorial) `<nixpkgs/nixos>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:119
msgid ""
"The [`-A` option](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/stable/command-ref/opt-common."
"html#opt-attr) specifies the attribute to pick from the provided Nix "
"expression `<nixpkgs/nixos>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:121
msgid ""
"To build the virtual machine, we choose the `vm` attribute as defined in "
"[`nixos/default.nix`](https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/"
"blob/7c164f4bea71d74d98780ab7be4f9105630a2eba/nixos/default.nix#L19)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:123
msgid ""
"The [`-I` option](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/stable/command-ref/opt-common."
"html#opt-I) prepends entries to the search path."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:125
msgid ""
"Here we set `nixpkgs` to refer to a [specific version of Nixpkgs](ref-"
"pinning-nixpkgs) and set `nix-config` to the `configuration.nix` file in the "
"current directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:128
msgid "Running the virtual machine"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:130
msgid ""
"The previous command created a link with the name `result` in the working "
"directory. It links to the directory that contains the virtual machine."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:133
msgid ""
"$ ls -R ./result\n"
"result:\n"
"bin  system\n"
"\n"
"result/bin:\n"
"run-nixos-vm\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:142
msgid "Run the virtual machine:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:144
msgid ""
"$ QEMU_KERNEL_PARAMS=console=ttyS0 ./result/bin/run-nixos-vm -nographic; "
"reset\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:148
msgid ""
"This command will run QEMU in the current terminal due to `-nographic`. "
"`console=ttyS0` will also show the boot process, which ends at the console "
"login screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:151
msgid ""
"Log in as `alice` with the password `test`. Check that the programs are "
"indeed available as specified:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:154
msgid "$ cowsay hello | lolcat\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:158
msgid "Exit the virtual machine by shutting it down:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:160
msgid "$ sudo poweroff\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:165
msgid ""
"If you forgot to add the user to `wheel` or didn't set a password, stop the "
"virtual machine from a different terminal:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:167
msgid "$ sudo pkill qemu\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:172
msgid ""
"Running the virtual machine will create a `nixos.qcow2` file in the current "
"directory. This disk image file contains the dynamic state of the virtual "
"machine. It can interfere with debugging as it keeps the state of previous "
"runs, for example the user password."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:176
msgid "Delete this file when you change the configuration:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:178
msgid "$ rm nixos.qcow2\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:182
msgid "Running GNOME on a graphical VM"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:184
msgid ""
"To create a virtual machine with a graphical user interface, add the "
"following lines to the configuration:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:186
msgid ""
"  # Enable the X11 windowing system.\n"
"  services.xserver.enable = true;\n"
"\n"
"  # Enable the GNOME Desktop Environment.\n"
"  services.xserver.displayManager.gdm.enable = true;\n"
"  services.xserver.desktopManager.gnome.enable = true;\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:195
msgid ""
"These three lines activate X11, the GDM display manager (to be able to "
"login) and Gnome as desktop manager."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:199
msgid ""
"You can also use the `installation-cd-graphical-gnome.nix` module to "
"generate the configuration file from scratch:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:201
msgid ""
"nix-shell -I nixpkgs=channel:nixos-24.05 -p \"$(cat <<EOF\n"
"  let\n"
"    pkgs = import <nixpkgs> { config = {}; overlays = []; };\n"
"    iso-config = pkgs.path + /nixos/modules/installer/cd-dvd/installation-cd-"
"graphical-gnome.nix;\n"
"    nixos = pkgs.nixos iso-config;\n"
"  in nixos.config.system.build.nixos-generate-config\n"
"EOF\n"
")\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:212
msgid "$ nixos-generate-config --dir ./\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:220
msgid ""
"{ config, pkgs, ... }:\n"
"{\n"
"  boot.loader.systemd-boot.enable = true;\n"
"  boot.loader.efi.canTouchEfiVariables = true;\n"
"\n"
"  services.xserver.enable = true;\n"
"\n"
"  services.xserver.displayManager.gdm.enable = true;\n"
"  services.xserver.desktopManager.gnome.enable = true;\n"
"\n"
"  users.users.alice = {\n"
"    isNormalUser = true;\n"
"    extraGroups = [ \"wheel\" ];\n"
"    initialPassword = \"test\";\n"
"  };\n"
"\n"
"  system.stateVersion = \"24.05\";\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:241
msgid ""
"To get graphical output, run the virtual machine without special options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:243
msgid ""
"$ nix-build '<nixpkgs/nixos>' -A vm -I nixpkgs=channel:nixos-24.05 -I nixos-"
"config=./configuration.nix\n"
"$ ./result/bin/run-nixos-vm\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:248
msgid "Running Sway as Wayland compositor on a VM"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:250
msgid ""
"To change to a Wayland compositor, disable `services.xserver.desktopManager."
"gnome` and enable `programs.sway`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:252
msgid "configuration.nix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:252
msgid ""
"-  services.xserver.desktopManager.gnome.enable = true;\n"
"+  programs.sway.enable = true;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:259
msgid ""
"Running Wayland compositors in a virtual machine might lead to complications "
"with the display drivers used by QEMU. You need to choose from the available "
"drivers one that is compatible with Sway. See [QEMU User Documentation]"
"(https://www.qemu.org/docs/master/system/qemu-manpage.html) for options. One "
"possibility is the `virtio-vga` driver:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:264
msgid "$ ./result/bin/run-nixos-vm -device virtio-vga\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:268
msgid "Arguments to QEMU can also be added to the configuration file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:270
msgid ""
"{ config, pkgs, ... }:\n"
"{\n"
"  boot.loader.systemd-boot.enable = true;\n"
"  boot.loader.efi.canTouchEfiVariables = true;\n"
"\n"
"  services.xserver.enable = true;\n"
"\n"
"  services.xserver.displayManager.gdm.enable = true;\n"
"  programs.sway.enable = true;\n"
"\n"
"  imports = [ <nixpkgs/nixos/modules/virtualisation/qemu-vm.nix> ];\n"
"  virtualisation.qemu.options = [\n"
"    \"-device virtio-vga\"\n"
"  ];\n"
"\n"
"  users.users.alice = {\n"
"    isNormalUser = true;\n"
"    extraGroups = [ \"wheel\" ];\n"
"    initialPassword = \"test\";\n"
"  };\n"
"\n"
"  system.stateVersion = \"24.05\";\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/nixos-configuration-on-vm.md:298
msgid ""
"The NixOS manual has chapters on [X11](https://nixos.org/manual/nixos/stable/"
